A couple of quick notes on the next block of code:

I'm using a HuggingFace utility called TextStreamer so that results stream back. To stream results, we simply replace: outputs = model.generate(inputs, max_new_tokens=80) With: streamer = TextStreamer(tokenizer) outputs = model.generate(inputs, max_new_tokens=80, streamer=streamer)

Also I've added the argument add_generation_prompt=True to my call to create the Chat template. This ensures that Phi generates a response to the question, instead of just predicting how the user prompt continues. Try experimenting with setting this to False to see what happens. You can read about this argument here:

https://huggingface.co/docs/transformers/main/en/chat_templating#what-are-generation-prompts

Thank you to student Piotr B for raising the issue!


